Efficacy of anticancer alkylphosphocholines in Trypanosoma brucei subspecies.

Konstantinov SM(1), Kaminsky R, Brun R, Berger MR, Zillmann U.

Author information:
(1)AG Toxikologie und Chemotherapie, Deutsches Krebsforschungszentrum, 
Heidelberg, Germany.

Tetradecylphosphocholine (TPC), hexadecylphosphocholine (HPC), 
hexadecylphospho(N-N-N-trimethyl)hexanolamine (HPC6), octadecylphosphocholine 
(OPC), and octadecyl-[2-(N-methylpiperidinio)ethyl]-phosphate (OMPEP) were 
investigated for antitrypanosomal activity in vitro and in vivo. OMPEP showed 
