523. Health Rep. 1996 Autumn;8(2):7-10(Eng); 7-11(Fre).

Dementia among seniors.

[Article in English, French]

Hill G(1), Forbes W, Berthelot JM, Lindsay J, McDowell I.

Author information:
(1)Social and Economic Studies Division at Statistics Canada, Ottawa.

The prevalence of dementia increases sharply in old age and is higher among 
women than men. Alzheimer's disease, the most common form of dementia, affects a 
greater proportion of women. On average, the number of years lived with dementia 
is longer for women, and women with dementia are more likely to be living in 
institutions than men with the condition.

